      "section": "3.2.3 Applications of Attention in our Model",
      "source_kind": "paragraph",
      "span_text": "• The encoder contains self-attention layers. In a self-attention layer all of the keys, values and queries come from the same place, in this case, the output of the previous layer in the encoder. Each position in the encoder can attend to all positions in the previous layer of the encoder.",
